    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Graz, 13 December 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>1. Although he wants to spare Oláh because he knows Oláh is unwell, he
                            still has to summon him to his court as soon as his health permits, he
                            should come to Bruck an der Mur, which is six miles away, and he should
                            let him know when he has arrived. From there he should only take his
                            immediate accompaniment to the court. 2. Oláh knows that King Ferdinand
                            I has summoned Lestár Feledi to make him Captain of Košice, but because
                            no answer has arrived from him since then, King Ferdinand I asks Oláh to
                            inform him as soon as he learns anything, or if he has not received King
                            Ferdinand I’s letter, Oláh should send it to him again; King Ferdinand I
                            can namely not tolerate Košice remaining without a captain.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime in Christo Pater, <del corresp="scriba"
                        >Devote</del> Fidelis nobis Dilecte!</p>
                <p>[1.] Quamquam infirmitati, <del corresp="scriba">Tuae</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="insert">qua Devotionem Tuam impediri audivimus</add>,
                    pro ea clementia, qua Devotionem Tuam prosequimur, libenter admodum parceremus,
                    ne <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied><corr>enim</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> viae et rigidi temporis molestia subscribenda esset, attamen cum
                    Devotionis Tuae opera et praesentia hoc tempore in pertractandis arduis
                    gravissimisque tam publicis quam privatis regni nostri Hungariae negotiis
                    summopere indignamus, non potuimus praetermittere, quin Devotionem Tuam <del
                        corresp="scriba">hac</del> ad nos <del corresp="scriba">et</del> in aulam
                    hanc nostram regiam evocaremus, <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">etiamsi
                        eandem sua sponte non diutius quam per imbecillitatem expedire emansuram
                        esse credamus.</add> Devotioni Tuae <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">ob
                        id</add> gratiose iniungentes, <del corresp="scriba"><gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"
                                /></del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">ut quamprimum</add> sive suae
                    valetudinis incommodo fieri poterit, <del corresp="scriba">quod</del> sese <del
                        corresp="scriba">citra ullam moram</del> in viam det atque huc ad nos
                    veniat, ita tamen quando in oppidum nostrum <del corresp="scriba"
                        >Bruck</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        ><placeName>Pruck</placeName></add>,<note type="critic">Bruck an der
                        Mur.</note> quod sex miliaribus hinc abest, appulerit, <add corresp="scriba"
                        type="insert">paucis</add> aliquot istic diebus moram trahat. Donec de
                    adventu suo <del corresp="scriba">a Devotione Tua</del> certiores reddamur,
                    prout nos illico <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">etiam Devotio Tua de
                        eo</add> certiorem reddere debebit, <del corresp="scriba">ut ita</del>
                    postea <del corresp="scriba">sic</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        >vero</add> a nobis admonita <del corresp="scriba"><gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"
                                /></del><add corresp="scriba" type="insert">iuxta ordinationem a nobis
                        dandam</add> minori qua poterit familia et comitiva propter praesentium
                    temporum periculum ad aulam nostram regiam <del corresp="scriba">accomodare
                        queat sicut et alii offocales et ministri facere poterant</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">accomodat</add>.<note type="critic">See Ep.
                        833.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15521206_1</ref>
                </p>
                <p>[2.] Deinde Devotio <del corresp="scriba">Vestra</del> Tua non ignorat
                        <persName>Eustachium a Veledy</persName><note type="critic">Lestár
                        Feledi.</note> in regiam <milestone unit="pb"/>aulam nostram evocatum fuisse hac de causa, ut ei <persName>capitaneum
                        Cassoviensem</persName><note type="critic">Until 1552, György Serédy was
                        Captain of Košice, Feledi became his successor.</note>
                    <del corresp="scriba">conferat</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        >conferamus</add>. Posteaquam autem nobis (quatenus <del corresp="scriba"
                        >nobis</del> nos cognitum habemus) nullum plane responsum ab ipso <del
                        corresp="scriba">nobis</del> relatum est, <add corresp="scriba"
                        type="insert">nostrum autem plurimi intersit, ut praefatae civitati nostrae
                        Cassoviensi de capitaneo tempestive provideatur</add>
                    de<gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/> Devotioni Tuae benigniter committimus, si responsum aliquod ab ipso
                    accepisset, quod nos de eo evestigio informet, sin autem nihil dum ab ipso
                    accepisset, <del corresp="scriba">quod</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        >volumus quidem, Tua Devotio</add> eo illico per proprium nuntium rescribat
                    et exemplum priorum litterarum nostrarum transmittat, denuo firmissime iste <del
                        corresp="scriba">mandat</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        >mandando</add>, quae citra omnem moram aut largi<gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/>
                    nem sese in aulam nostram regiam conferat, prout summa rei necessitas
                    postulat. Non possumus enim <del corresp="scriba"> diutius concedere</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">ferre</add>, quod
                        <placeName>Cassovia</placeName><note type="critic">Košice.</note> diutius
                    quam parsi<gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/> capitaneo careat. In eis Devotio Tua factura <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied><corr>sit</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> nobis rem maxime gratam clementia nostra regia erga ipsum
                    recognoscenda.</p>
                <p>Datum <placeName>Grätz</placeName> 13. Decembris 1552.</p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Reverendissimo in Christo patri Nicolao Olaho episcopo Agriensi nostro
                    consiliario et per regnum nostrum Hungariae cancellario devoto fideli nobis
                    dilecto.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
